# TypeScript Conventions

## Multi-Tenant Scoping
Every database query MUST include `merchant_id` filtering:
```typescript
// Always scope by merchant
const { data } = await db.from('loyalty_customers')
  .select('*')
  .eq('merchant_id', merchant.id);
```

## Hono Route Pattern
Routes receive merchant context via `c.get('merchant')`:
```typescript
const merchant = c.get('merchant');  // DbMerchant from middleware
const db = getSupabase(c.env);
const cc = CloudCartClient.forMerchant(merchant);
```

## CloudCart API Client
- Use `CloudCartClient.forMerchant(merchant)` — never construct manually
- Base URL auto-appends `/api/v2`
- All requests use JSON:API format (`data.type`, `data.attributes`)

## Error Handling
- CloudCart client throws on non-2xx — wrap in try/catch
- Return `c.json({ error: message }, statusCode)` for API errors
- Log with `console.error(\`[\${slug}] message\`)` for webhook debugging

## Types
- All DB row types are in `src/types.ts` (prefixed with `Db`)
- CloudCart types are prefixed with `CC`
- Env bindings type: `Env`, context variables: `AppVariables`
